Preheat your oven to 200°C. Bring a large #pot of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the pasta. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 5cm pieces. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 3cm sized chunks. Halve, peel and cut the @red onion{1} into wedges. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all).

Pop the aubergine onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and scatter over half the @dried Italian herbs{1/2}. Toss to coat then roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking. Meanwhile, pop the red onion, pepper and @baby plum tomatoes{125} onto another baking tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and scatter over the remaining Italian herbs. Toss to coat. Roast on the middle shelf for the final ~{15%minutes} of the aubergine cooking time.

Once the pan of water has come to the boil, add the @penne pasta{200%g} and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Heat a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil.) Once the pan is hot, add the @chorizo{60%g} and stir-fry until it releases its lovely red oil, ~{1-2%minutes}. Don't let it take on too much colour! Add the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} carefully, bring to a simmer then tip into a large #bowl and mix with the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} into chunks.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander then add to the bowl with the chorizo dressing. Mix well to coat then stir through the roasted pepper, tomato, onion, half the feta, half the aubergine and half the parsley. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide the pasta salad between your plates. Top with the remaining aubergine, feta and parsley. Enjoy!